<title>USA: Sterling Software Q1 Dec 31 net shr $0.33.</title>
<headline>Sterling Software Q1 Dec 31 net shr $0.33.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-02-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three Months</p>
<p>							Ended December 31</p>
<p>							 1996	 1995</p>
<p>Revenue					     $97,141   $95,985</p>
<p>Net income from continuing operations	12,740     9,018</p>
<p>Income from discontinued operations,</p>
<p> net of taxes (A)						12,289</p>
<p>Income applicable to common stockholders   12,740    21,307</p>
<p>Earnings from continuing operations</p>
<p> per common share (B)				$.33	$.30</p>
<p>Earnings per common share (B)		    $.33	$.66</p>
<p>Average common shares outstanding (000's)  38,439    26,630</p>
<p>Notes:</p>
<p>(A) On September 30, 1996, Sterling Software completed the spin-off of Sterling Commerce Inc. (Sterling Commerce) with the pro rata distribution of its remaining 81.6 percent ownership in Sterling Commerce to Sterling Software's shareholders by means of a tax-free dividend.  </p>
<p>Accordingly, Sterling Software's results of operations for fiscal 1996 reflect the reclassification of Sterling Commerce, previously a wholly owned subsidiary of Sterling Software, as a discontinued operation.</p>
<p>(B)  On a fully diluted basis.</p>
<p>Full company name is Sterling Software Inc.</p>
<p>(in $ thousands, except per share data)</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212 859-1610))</p>
